name: Rising Seas
description:
Returning to the car before work after a quick jaunt around Ōtāhuhu / Mount Richmond, one of Auckland’s many extinct volcanoes and an island of nature in built up and industrialised South Auckland.

Ōtāhuhu sits on a narrow isthmus of land between the seas to east and west and was used way back by Māori as a portage for canoes (Waka).
